\h Yirmeyah
\toc1 Yirmeyah
\toc2 Yirmeyah
\toc3 Yer.
\mt1 Yirmeyah
\mt2 (Jeremiah)
\is1 Introduction
\ip The prophet Yirmeyah/Jeremiah, started his vocation as a prophet around 627 B.C. and continued for just under fifty years until around 580 B.C. Te long time of serving Yirmeyah, impanpanayan he/his the people concerning the destruction coming of nation due to sins their, and of worshipping ran of false gods. And/Now saw of Yirmeyah the katumanan of prophesied he/his of time nasakup e the Yerushalem of Nibukadnisar King of Babylon. Saw/Found his again the demolition of city and temple, and the capture of many people other of King their there to Babylon. Prophesied he/his again the return of people from capture their, and the replacement of standing up of nation there to old natahuan here.
\ip \bk The Account of Yirmeyah\bk* divided of five main sections: 1. The calling to Yirmeyah; 2. the what was said of God for of nation of Yehudah and of teachers here at time of kingdom of Husiyas, Huwakim, Hihuyakin and of Sidikiyas; 3. the all persecution of people according to it's written of Baruk secretary of Yirmeyah, including the various prophecies, and the important what happened of life of Yirmeyah; 4. the what was said of Master God concerning the various foreigner there nations; and 5. the other still story concerning the demolition of Yerushalem, and of pegkaddakep of people going to Babylon.
\ip Merciful person Yirmeyah; very his love the his people, and disliked he/his the judging them. There are parts of document very the love his of telling concerning the sufferings he/his due to because called he of God so that to become prophets. Like fire there to heart he/his the speech of Master God, and not he/his indeed this igkeeles.
\ip Written again of this document coming the time there is e new agreement. And/Now the that agreement eg-ay-ayaran of people of God and obeyed their, even still not/none teacher thinking them because written man e this there to me heart their. (31:31-34)
\iot Main components of this document
\io1 Yirmeyah's calling \ior 1:1-19\ior*
\io1 The prophecies concerning the kingdom of Husiyas, Huwakim, Huwakin, and of Sidikiyas \ior 2:1РђЊ25:38\ior*
\io1 Yirmeyah's persecution \ior 26:1РђЊ45:5\ior*
\io1 The prophecies for nations \ior 46:1РђЊ51:64\ior*
\io1 Yerushalem's destruction \ior 52:1-34\ior*
\rem This is still a very early look into the unfinished text of the Open English Translation of the Bible. Please double-check the text in advance before using in public.
\ie
\c 1
\p
\v 1 \add These are\add* the messages┬д304124 from Hilkiyah's son, YirmeyahРђћone of the priests┬д304131 who were in Anatot┬д304133 in Benyamin's┬д304135 territory┬д304134.
\v 2 Yahweh's┬д304141 messages┬д304139 \add started\add* coming to him when Yehudah's┬д304149 King┬д304148 Yoshiyah \add (Josiah,\add* Amon's┬д304147 son) was in the thirteenth year┬д304153 of his reign┬д304154.\x + \xo 1:2: \xt 2Ki 22:3РђЊ23:27; 2Ch 34:8РђЊ35:19.\x*
\v 3 \add РЅѕIt continued\add* through the \add РЅѕreign\add* of Yoshiyah's son, King Yehoyakim \add (Jehoiakim)\add* until the end of the eleventh year of \add the reign\add* of Yoshiyah's son, King Tsidkiyah \add (Hezekiah)\add*РђћYerushalem┬д304179 \add (Jerusalem)\add* was exiled┬д304178 in the fifth┬д304181 month┬д304180 \add of that year\add*.\x + \xo 1:3: a \xt 2Ki 23:36РђЊ24:7; 2Ch 36:5-8; \xo b \xt 2Ki 24:18РђЊ25:21; 2Ch 36:11-21.\x*
\s1 Yirmeyah's calling
\rem /s1 Jeremiah's Call and First Visions; Jeremiah's call and first visions; Jeremiah's Call and Commission; The Call of Jeremiah
\q1
\v 4 \add РЅѕNow\add* Yahweh's┬д304187 message┬д304185 came to me:
\q1
\v 5 РђюBefore┬д304191 I formed┬д304192 you in \add РЅѕyour mother\add*, I \add already\add* knew┬д304195 you,
\q1 РЅѕand before┬д304196 you came┬д304197 out of the womb, I \add РЅѕhad a plan for you\add*.
\q1 I appointed┬д304202 you as a prophet┬д304200 to the nations┬д304201.РђЮ
\p
\v 6 \add РЅѕBut┬д304204\add* I said┬д304204, РђюOh no, Yahweh┬д304206, my master┬д304206. Listen, I don't┬д304209 know┬д304211 how to speak┬д304212, because┬д304214 I'm \add just\add* a young lad.РђЮ
\p
\v 7 \add РЅѕbut┬д304220\add* Yahweh┬д304221 told me, РђюDon't┬д304223 say that you're only a child, because┬д304228 you must go┬д304235 to everyone I send you to and you must tell them everything that I command┬д304240 you to say.
\v 8 Don't┬д304243 be afraid┬д304245 of them, because┬д304247 I'll be with you to rescue┬д304251 you.РђЮ
\m That's Yahweh's┬д304254 message┬д304252.
\p
\v 9 Then┬д304256 Yahweh┬д304257 stretched┬д304256 out his hand┬д304260 and touched┬д304261 my mouth and said, РђюListen┬д304266, I've┬д304269 put my messages into your mouth.
\v 10 I'm┬д304274 appointing┬д304274 you┬д304274 today over the nations┬д304280 and kingdoms┬д304283Рђћto uproot and to break down, to destroy┬д304286 and to pull down, to build┬д304288 and to plant┬д304289.РђЮ
\s1 Yahweh encourages Yirmeyah
\rem /s1 Two Visions
\p
\v 11 \add РЅѕAnother time,\add* Yahweh's┬д304295 message┬д304293 came to me, saying, РђюYirmeyah \add (Jeremiah)\add*, what do you┬д304300 see?РђЮ
\p РђюI see a branch┬д304304 from an almond┬д304305 tree┬д304305,РђЮ I \add РЅѕreplied\add*.
\p
\v 12 Then┬д304309 Yahweh┬д304310 told me, РђюYou've done┬д304312 well to see┬д304313 \add <that\add*, because┬д304314 I keep watch\f + \fr 1:12 \ft There's a play on words in the original here, as the Hebrew word for Рђўkeeping watchРђЎ has the same consonants as the word for РђўalmondРђЎ.\f* on my message┬д304320 \add РЅѕto make sure it happens\add*.РђЮ
\p
\v 13 Then Yahweh┬д304327 asked me a second┬д304330 time what I was seeing, and I replied, РђюI see a pot full of boiling water and it's tipping towards the north┬д304342.РђЮ
\p
\v 14 Рђю\add Yes,\add* disaster will come from the north┬д304347 \add and┬д304344\add* be released onto all the inhabitants┬д304353 of this region,РђЮ Yahweh┬д304345 \add РЅѕcontinued┬д304344\add*.
\v 15 РђюListen, I'm about┬д304359 to summon┬д304359 all the clans┬д304362 of the northern┬д304364 kingdoms┬д304363, and they'll come┬д304368 and \add attack\add* the walls┬д304379 around┬д304380 Yerushalem and all of Yehudah's┬д304385 \add other\add* cities┬д304384, then each \add @king\add* will place his throne┬д304371 at the entrance┬д304372 to Yerushalem's┬д304375 gates┬д304374.РђЮ That is Yahweh's┬д304367 declaration.
\v 16 Рђю\add That's how\add* I'll┬д304387 judge┬д304388 \add @my people\add* for their wickedness┬д304393 as they've abandoned┬д304395 me and \add РЅѕsacrificed┬д304396\add* to other┬д304398 gods┬д304397 and bowed┬д304399 down to \add idols\add* that┬д304394 they made with their own hands┬д304401.
\v 17 \add РЅѕSo┬д304403\add* \add @Yirmeyah\add*, \add РЅѕget yourself ready┬д304404 and go\add* and tell them everything that I'll tell you. Don't┬д304415 be scared┬д304417 \add РЅѕin front of them\add* or else I'll scare you \add right there\add* \add РЅѕin front of them\add*!
\v 18 And listen, today I've┬д304426 you┬д304426 \add as strong as\add* a fortified┬д304429 city┬д304428 and an iron pillar┬д304430 and bronze┬д304433 walls┬д304432, as far as the kings┬д304439 of Yehudah┬д304440 \add are concerned\add*, along with their officials┬д304441 and priests┬д304442, and the \add РЅѕgeneral population\add*.
\v 19 They'll \add РЅѕoppose\add* you \add РЅѕbut┬д304446\add* they won't┬д304448 \add be able to\add* defeat you because┬д304452 I'll be with you to rescue┬д304459 you,РђЮ says Yahweh┬д304458.
\c 2
\s1 Yisrael has deviated from Yahweh
\rem /s1 God's appeal to Israel and Judah; The Lord's Case against His People; God Pleads with Israel to Repent; Israel Forsakes God; God's Care for Israel
\p
\v 1 Then Yahweh┬д304465 \add РЅѕgave\add* me a message┬д304463
\v 2 to proclaim┬д304470 to Yerushalem's┬д304473 ears┬д304471:
\q1 РђюYahweh┬д304477 says┬д304476: I remember┬д304478 your loyal┬д304480 commitment \add РЅѕwhen you were all young\add*
\q1 РЅѕand your love┬д304482 \add РЅѕwhen you were committed to me\add*.
\q1 You all followed after┬д304485 me in the wilderness┬д304486 \add РЅѕwhere no crops were planted\add*.
\q1
\v 3 Yisrael┬д304492 was set apart for Yahweh┬д304493Рђћthe firstfruits of his harvest.
\q1 All those┬д304499 who devoured┬д304499 it became guilty┬д304500Рђћcalamity┬д304501 came to them.
\q1 That is Yahweh's┬д304493 declaration.
\s1 The sin of ancestors of Israelis
\rem /s1 The Sin of Israel's Ancestors
\p
\v 4 Listen to Yahweh's┬д304512 message┬д304510 you \add РЅѕdescendants\add* of Yakov \add (Jacob)\add*,
\q1 РЅѕand┬д304515 all you clans┬д304517 \add РЅѕthat are part\add* of Yisrael┬д304519 \add (Israel┬д304519)\add*.
\q1
\v 5 Yahweh┬д304524 asks: what injustices┬д304530 did you ancestors┬д304528 find in me,
\q1 that \add caused them\add* to become distant┬д304532 from me.
\q1 They \add РЅѕchased\add* after┬д304535 vanity┬д304536 and became vain.
\q1
\v 6 They didn't┬д304539 \add РЅѕtry to find out\add* where┬д304541 Yahweh┬д304542 wasРђћ
\q1 \add the one\add* brought┬д304543 led them out of Egypt┬д304546 \add (Heb. Mitsrayim)\add*
\q1 then┬д304539 led them \add РЅѕthrough\add* the wilderness with its pits and┬д304539 desert areas.
\q1 \add It was\add* a \add РЅѕregion┬д304545\add* of deep darkness┬д304555 \add РЅѕwithout water\add*Рђћ
\q1 an \add РЅѕarea\add* that┬д304557 no one passes┬д304559 through, \add РЅѕlet alone\add* lives in.
\q1
\v 7 Then┬д304568 I took you to the Carmel \add РЅѕregion┬д304572\add*
\q1 to eat┬д304574 its fruit┬д304575 and \add other\add* good┬д304576 things┬д304576.
\q1 \add РЅѕHowever\add* you came┬д304577 and defiled my land
\q1 РЅѕand made the inheritance┬д304582 \add РЅѕthat I gave you\add* into \add РЅѕsomething detestable\add*.
\q1
\v 8 The priests┬д304586 didn't ask where┬д304589 Yahweh┬д304590 was,
\q1 and the handlers┬д304591 of the law didn't know me.
\q1 The shepherds┬д304595 rebelled┬д304596 against┬д304597 me,
\q1 and the prophets prophesied by Ba'al
\q1 and they went after┬д304601 \add things┬д304602\add* that┬д304602 wouldn't profit┬д304604 them.
\s1 Yahweh's case against his people
\rem /s1 The Lord's Case against His People
\q1
\v 9 Yahweh┬д304613 declares: I┬д304618 will bring a case against you all,
\q1 and I'll┬д304609 contend against your \add children and\add* your grandchildren.
\q1
\v 10 If you all cross┬д304621 over \add west\add* to the coasts┬д304622 of Cypress \add island\add* and look,
\q1 or head \add east\add* to Kedar┬д304625, \add РЅѕask around\add* and \add РЅѕpay careful┬д304627 attention\add*
\q1 to see if something like this has \add ever\add* happened┬д304631 \add before\add*.
\q1
\v 11 Has a country┬д304635 ever \add РЅѕswapped out\add* its gods (not that┬д304643 they were \add actual\add* gods)?
\q1 \add РЅѕBut┬д304637\add* my people┬д304640 have exchanged their \add РЅѕgreatness\add* for something \add РЅѕof no benefit\add*.
\q1
